Former President Olusegun Obasanjo, on Wednesday, decorated his son, Adeboye, with the latter’s new rank of brigadier-general. The event took place at the headquarters of the Nigerian Army engineer corps in Lagos. Adeboye’s decoration with the new rank followed his recent promotion from colonel to brigadier-general in the Nigerian Army. Meanwhile, Obasanjo, who is a two-term civilian ruler and former military head of state, is a retired general of the Nigerian Army. See photo below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-652679" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo.jpeg" alt="" width="780" height="470" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo.jpeg 780w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo-300x181.jpeg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo-768x463.jpeg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo-24x14.jpeg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo-36x22.jpeg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Olu-Obasanjo-48x29.jpeg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" />